text:
Valgrind report memory leaks when creating multithreaded applications (with at least num threads > 3 in my case) in libthr.s.3 in which threads are created in DETACHED state.

Application memory usage steadly increase during thread creation, and this extra memory is never released.

This problem affect server processed based on creation of pools of detached threads. After running for hours or a few days the process can grow to very high memory usage and need to be restarted.

This problem does not appear in

How-To-Repeat: A simple thread creation c program:

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <unistd.h>
#include <pthread.h>

#define KB 1024
#define MB 1024*KB
#define NUM_THREADS 1000
#define PTHREAD_STACK_SIZE 1*MB

void *dosomething( void* data ) 
{
  printf("%ld something\n", (long int)data);
  pthread_exit(NULL);

  return NULL;
}

int main() 
{
  pthread_t th[NUM_THREADS];
  pthread_attr_t attr[NUM_THREADS];

  long int i;
  for (i = 0; i < NUM_THREADS; i++) 
  {
    pthread_attr_init(&attr[i]);
    pthread_attr_setstacksize(&attr[i], PTHREAD_STACK_SIZE);
    pthread_attr_setdetachstate(&attr[i], PTHREAD_CREATE_DETACHED);
    pthread_create(&th[i], &attr[i], dosomething, (void*)i);
    pthread_attr_destroy(&attr[i]);

    if (((i+1)%25)==0) {
      sleep(1);
    }
  }

  sleep(10);

  pthread_exit(0);							  
  return 0;
}

monitor "top -U username" the process in 9.0R and 8.3R to see the different behaviour.
